HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1539
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to recognize and honor Dickson County Mayor
Robert "Bob" Rial on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those public servants who have rendered dedicated, effective, and visionary leadership to their
communities; and
WHEREAS, Robert "Bob" Rial was first elected County Mayor of Dickson County in
August 2010, earning fifty-four percent of the vote in a four-way race, and he was subsequently
reelected in 2014, 2018, and 2022, serving with distinction from September 1, 2010, through
August 30, 2026; and
WHEREAS, prior to his service as County Mayor, Bob Rial devoted twenty-seven years
to a career in finance and banking and served the citizens of the City of Dickson as a member of
the Dickson City Council from 2003 through 2010; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Rial is a graduate of Dickson County High School and the University
of Tennessee at Martin, where he earned a degree in Public Administration and a certificate in
Government Management from the International City/County Management Association; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure as County Mayor, Bob Rial demonstrated a steadfast
commitment to professional development and excellence in public administration by earning the
designations of Certified Public Administrator and Tennessee Certified Economic Developer
through coursework at the University of Tennessee Institute for Public Service, an achievement
that is notably rare for a county official; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Rial is also a graduate of the Harvard University Kennedy School of
Government program for Senior Executives in State and Local Government, further reflecting
his dedication to informed, innovative, and ethical leadership; and
