WHEREAS, throughout his tenure, Mayor Rial has overseen and delivered a remarkable
record of accomplishments on behalf of Dickson County, including resolving an inherited $130
million federal lawsuit related to the County's landfill by leveraging other public and private
contributions, all without increasing County taxes; constructing a new $25 million Justice Center
in Charlotte; and establishing a long-range and sustainable plan for funding school construction
projects, improving school security, increasing financial support for education including teacher
compensation, and strengthening relationships between the County and its school system; and
WHEREAS, his accomplishments as mayor further include facilitating Project Falcon
(Dal-Tile), the largest capital investment in county history, in addition to other major industrial
projects, including Zinc Oxide, Dal Quartz, National Cement, and assisting with expansions of
existing industries such as Metrican and Zochem; expanding emergency medical services
countywide; developing a new Highway Department complex and Emergency Management
Agency facility in Charlotte on the former Eubank site; constructing a new Health Department
facility in the City of Dickson; renovating the historic courthouse and jailer's house; and
constructing a new Planning and Zoning building on the square in Charlotte; and
WHEREAS, he also played an important role in purchasing and developing a new
county library and office complex in the City of Dickson; developing a new farmers market
facility in downtown Dickson; expanding and improving county convenience centers, archives,
and numerous other public facilities; acquiring land and completing design work for a future
County Agricultural Center; providing new equipment, vehicles, and a dedicated funding stream
for Volunteer Fire Departments and Emergency Management Services; and securing State
Industrial Access Road funding, rail spur extensions, and other infrastructure improvements to
attract and retain industry; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Rial eliminated debt related to the County's industrial park and
expanded the inventory of county-owned industrial property to enhance economic
- 2 - 018357

competitiveness; provided leadership to and served regional partners, including the Mid
Cumberland Human Resource Agency, the Greater Nashville Regional Council, and the Rural
Planning Organization (RPO); served the State of Tennessee through appointments by
Governor Bill Haslam and Governor Bill Lee to the Tennessee Underground Storage Tanks and
Solid Waste Disposal Control Board and service on the Tennessee Advisory Commission on
Intergovernmental Relations; secured grant funding for roadway paving and critical bridge
replacement projects, including Community Development Block Grant funding for the Piney
River Bridge; established a self-funded Enterprise Fund for the operation of the County's landfill;
and reorganized the County Ambulance Service to improve efficiency and cost effectiveness;
and
WHEREAS, he provided consistent investment in county roads, bridges, and
infrastructure throughout Dickson County; improved inmate healthcare services while reducing
overall operational costs; implemented a pay-as-you-go approach to capital projects and
maintained balanced county budgets passed on or ahead of schedule each year; and
developed, implemented, and refined a comprehensive employee compensation plan; and
WHEREAS, he also improved countywide law enforcement capabilities through
increased pay, upgraded vehicles and equipment, and improved facilities; updated zoning,
planning, and subdivision regulations, including completion of a comprehensive county growth
plan; collaborated on water and sewer system improvements throughout the County and
leveraging grant funding to expand these essential services; and served as the Capital
Campaign Honorary Chair to raise funds for, and awareness of, the Historic Promise Land
Community; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Rial further served the public by developing and presenting a
seminar entitled "County Government 101," providing multiple educational sessions to elected
- 3 - 018357

officials and the general public to promote transparency and understanding of county
government; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Rial's leadership has been characterized by integrity, fiscal
responsibility, strategic vision, and a collaborative approach that has significantly improved the
quality of life for the citizens of Dickson County and positioned the County for continued
success; and
WHEREAS, during his time in serving the County, Bob Rial has been blessed and
supported by his wife of forty-one years, Joan Rial; his two children, Daniel (Amanda) Rial and
Rebecca Rial; and his grandchild, Julien Patrick Rial; and
WHEREAS, throughout his service, Bob Rial has reflected great credit upon himself, his
family, the citizens of Dickson County, and the State of Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend County Mayor Robert "Bob" Rial for his
exemplary service and distinguished leadership as County Mayor of Dickson County from 2010
through 2026, extending our sincere appreciation and best wishes for continued happiness and
success in all his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
